Flowers were individually enclosed within PET film oven bags (Bratschlauch, Melitta GmbH, 
Germany
), from which scented air was drawn for 20–60 min by battery-operated vacuum pumps (model G 12/01 EB, ASF Thomas, Inc., 
Germany
) at a constant flow rate of 200 ml min 

–
1

. The volatiles in the air were trapped in glass tubes containing adsorbent polymer (
50 mg
), consisting of a 1:1 mixture of Tenax™ TA (80/100 mesh, Supelco, 
USA
) and Carbopack™ X (20/40 mesh, Supelco, 
USA
). Blanks obtained with air drawn from empty bags were simultaneously collected in each case. Immediately following scent collection, the adsorbent traps were eluted with hexane (250 µL; 

À

99.9% purity, Sigma–Aldrich, 
USA
) then kept at 
–
24 ° 
C
refrigeration until analysis.

